As
of today, the total number of confirmed coronavirus cases in Mzansi is standing at 11 350. Health
minister Dr Zweli Mkhize reported that there are 698 news cases in Mzansi on Tuesday. He
said the number of coronavirus deaths have risen to 206. The
number of recoveries in the country stands at 4357. A
total 369697 tests have been conducted thus far. Mkhize said: This outbreak will only be defeated if the community
understands the issues of hand washing, sanitising, coughing and sneezing into
your elbow etc. Each one of us can do something to reduce contracting the virus
and each one of us can do something to reduce the spread."  #COVID19 Statistics in SA as at 12 May 2020 pic.twitter.com/hqVjVNhQyw  #COVID19 Statistics in SA as at 12 May 2020 pic.twitter.com/hqVjVNhQyw  